r sugars based on their carbon chain, and in 1906, Rosanoﬀ chose the glyceraldehyde (which is a monosaccharide) as the reference for the stereochemistry of carbohydrates and other chiral molecules [Rosanoﬀ, 1906]. He then arbitrarily assigned the descriptor d (resp. l) to the (+)-glyceraldehyde (resp. (-

