3.2.3 Hydrolysis
RNA strands can be cleaved by hydrolysis, during which a phosphodiester bond of their backbone is broken. The cleavage rate is denoted kcut and is the same for all phosphodiester bonds in the system. Therefore any strand of length l is susceptible to be cleaved at one of its junctions with a rate (l − 1)kcut resulting in two shorter strands. However

